text: General elections were held in Sweden on 18 September 1960.Nohlen, D & Stöver, P (2010) Elections in Europe: A data handbook, p1858 The Swedish Social Democratic Party remained the largest party, winning 114 of the 232 seats in the Second Chamber of the Riksdag.Nohlen & Stöver, p1872 ==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right |- |colspan=7|300px |- !Party !Votes !% !Seats !+/– |- |align=left|Swedish Social Democratic Party||2,033,016||47.8||114||+3 |- |align=left|People's Party||744,142||17.5||40||+2 |- |align=left|Rightist Party||704,365||16.6||39||–6 |- |align=left|Centre Party||579,007||13.6||34||+2 |- |align=left|Communist Party of Sweden||190,560||4.5||5||0 |- |align=left|Other parties||3,024||0.0||0||0 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||17,496||–||–||– |- |align=left|Total||4,271,610||100||232||+1 |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||4,972,177||85.9||–||– |- |align=left colspan=5|Source: Nohlen & Stöver |} ==References== 1960 Category:1960 elections in Europe Category:1960 in Sweden Category:September 1960 events
